## Role Workflow

Spec reviews are performed by Goose using the recipes in `recipes/`.
Each role must complete its review before implementation begins.

| # | Role | Recipe | Reviews |
|---|------|--------|---------|
{% if roles %}
{% for role in roles %}
| {{ loop.index }} | {{ role.title }} | `{{ role.recipe }}` | {{ role.purpose }} |
{% endfor %}
{% else %}
| 1 | Architect | `recipes/architect.yaml` | System structure, tech stack, data flow |
| 2 | UI/UX Designer | `recipes/ui-designer.yaml` | CLI, config, env vars, error messages |
| 3 | Interface Designer | `recipes/interface-designer.yaml` | APIs, file formats, integration contracts |
| 4 | Security Analyst | `recipes/security-analyst.yaml` | Threat model, input validation, auth |
| 5 | Edge Case Analyst | `recipes/edge-case-analyst.yaml` | Boundary conditions, failure modes |
| 6 | Senior Developer | `recipes/senior-developer.yaml` | KISS review, task breakdown, test strategy |
{% endif %}

**Recipe usage:**
```bash
# Run a single role
goose run --recipe recipes/architect.yaml

# Run all roles in sequence (after prd.md is complete)
for recipe in recipes/architect.yaml recipes/ui-designer.yaml \
              recipes/interface-designer.yaml recipes/security-analyst.yaml \
              recipes/edge-case-analyst.yaml recipes/senior-developer.yaml; do
  goose run --recipe "$recipe"
done
```

